      been playing Ultimate up here for over 20 years. I passionately love
      Ultimate and the local and global community of players, and believe deeply
      in the principle of spirit of the game, challenging myself to live by it
      as best as I can in all areas of my life. To me that means always starting
      from an assumption of good will, focusing on the good I see in others,
      showing respect even when (especially when) I disagree with others, and
      trying to recognize as quickly as possible when I haven't been at my best
      so I can make amends.
    </p>
    <p>
      I love getting down to L.A. every January to play Ultimate on the beach,
      but my personal and political sensibilities are offended by everything
      I've described here. I started out assuming the best and believing that
      there is a good explanation for all the unknowns, but the more I've
      learned, the less I've been able or willing to keep that attitude.
    </p>
    <p>
      I had no idea about any of this until a few months ago, so figuring that
      probably lots of other folks still don't, and many of them might want to
      know, I decided to put together this web site. Although my biases are
      clear, I tried to be as fact-focused as possible and be clear about when
      I was speculating or expressing an opinion. If I screwed up and you want
      to call me out, or just express your opinions or ask questions, feel free
      to email me at {{#ext-a "mailto:ben@leioutconfidential.com"}}ben@leioutconfidential.com{{/ext-a}}
    </p>
